rComments: she lectures, then posts extra lectures online, giving us 2x the amount of work. she's sweet but has such high expectations on students. we have lives outside of orgo...

Dr. Flynn is an amazing lecturer that I strongly recommend. Orgo is undoubtedly a tough class but she really encourages active learning. She was understanding of the situation students are placed in when learning online. Her exams were tough, but she allowed weights to be shifted a lot. Don't be afraid to ask questions. Do your homework!

Dr. Flynn is a very understanding prof; she allowed us to shift the weight of midterms to the exam because of feedback from the students (e.g. midterm was too long , marking was inconsistent). Lots of grade boosters (weekly quizzes & participation marks). Midterms and exams were fair considering how difficult the material is.

Prof Flynn is honestly amazing. She is such a down to earth person and you can tell she really cares about her students success. She did everything she could to give everyone the best grade possible. The course content is pretty hard and she doesnt make her evaluations easy, but if you work hard you can do well. I would recommend orgo 2 with her!!

Idk why everyone is so mad at Flynn - she makes you think critically with her exams and I think that's a sign of a good professor. A lot of these reviewers must be used to the high inflation and easy marks of doing class online. Her exams are slightly hard but very fair and she is always open for discussion outside of class. Highly recommend.

Prof Flynn is nice and sweet and fun fine. but is that really only what students want in a prof LOL? I found her midterms to be really hard, quizzes are very easy and a good bump up to your grade along with participation and a few other minor things. Dont like her teaching style and do not like her brightspace AT ALL, very messy and unorganized.

Yes the course is hard and asynchronous learning sucks but she really cares about students. Midterm 1 was absurdly long so she made Midterm 2 much shorter. Midterm 2 had some marking issues with the TAs, so she re-graded every single exam herself and everyone's mark shot up. Exams are also unproctored and open book. Quizzes are grade boosters.

One of the nicest, down-to-earth profs I have ever had however, her exams were so tough and had way too many hard-level questions in such a short time period. Her teaching style is... unique to say the least. But again, she is such a nice professor who cares about the subject and her students but if you want a good grade, better try another prof.

Lots of harsh reviews on here, but Dr. Flynn is one of the most fair profs I've ever had. Course content is very very challenging, so expect to do a lot of work. Do the practice sets & midterms, the lectures are not sufficient. After some issues with MT2, Dr. Flynn personally reviewed ALL the midterms. Passionate about the subject & so nice.

nice woman, terrible teaching style that does not work for many students. spends too much time doing easy examples and marks very harshly on the midterms. Had an A+ in orgo 1 and have never struggled more for a good grade than I am right now in orgo2. Nachef is more difficult but at least the material is fair. switch out if you can!!

I didn't have high hopes for Orgo 2 - especially with the flipped classroom. But I ended up liking the teaching style (her videos were 3-7 minutes long each), very engaging lectures and if you did past papers/problem sets, the exams weren't too bad. She's very forgiving with the weight of exams and will give you the best possible grade.

I m writing this in tears. I wish i didn't take orgo 2 with her. My GPA is crying, the exams do not reflect the practice questions. I will never ever in my life take or advice anyone to take a class with her. I finished orgo 1 with A+ and here i am risking my gpa for orgo 2. I wish Dr Ogilvie was teaching this instead of her. At least he was fair
Insanely hard course which makes it even harder with Flynn. Her exam doesn't reflect the actual exam at all.

I managed to snag an A- in orgo 1 with a different prof, so I'm not bad at organic chem. However, Dr. Flynn's tests are SO hard. They take forever to do and the questions are the kinds you would skip when practicing because of their difficulty. Assignments and participation marks help keep your grade up, but still. This class will tank your GPA.

Dr Flynn is very nice and explains concepts pretty well. However, her "niceness" doesn't make up for her brutal tests. The first midterm was extremely difficult and I wouldn't be surprised if midterm 2 and the final are also hard. Only good thing is there are lots of participation marks and weekly quizzes that are easy to get 100 on.

Class midterm average was fifty eight percent. Shall I elaborate? If you want to pursue Sciences , avoid u of o. Is participating in her research study for marks without asking for our consent ethical? Would rather earn my marks through fair exams that reflect the difficulty of the material practiced in class like Dr. Ogilvie does.

Dr Flynn is sweet and fun ill give that to her but this class is death. Midterms are open book and a flipped classroom style. Midterms are CRAZY hard and honestly dont recommend her at all. People told me to run from el nachef for this class but I regret listening to them. Now im telling you.... RUN from THIS one!!!!!!!!

Obtained an A last year, dropped to a C on my first midterm. Really disappointed with how this class is going so far. Simple questions are explained in class but when the exams roll up, they're composed of really hard ones we have never discussed about. Wish I had taken this class in the french section as my friend told me it was 'a joke'. Regrets

Obtained an A last year, dropped to a C on my first midterm. Really disappointed with how this class is going so far. Simple questions are explained in class but when the exams roll up, they're composed of really hard ones we have never discussed about. Wish I had taken this class in the french section as my friend told me it was 'a joke'. Regrets.

Research between the English and the French Chem section shows that the French section is significantly easier than the English section. Dr. Flynn provides easy examples in class but tricks students on most questions on her lengthy exams. French exams by Dr. Keillor reflect what was taught in class. UOttawa needs to investigate this situation.
Says she loves teaching Organic II but all she's done so far is repost videos from previous years for us to watch asynchronously on our own time.

Horrible prof. Just goes over example problems in class and expects you to learn the material on your own before hand. Takes so long to reply to emails which is so discouraging as she never makes time to answer your questions in class anyways. The final and midterm 1 were crazy hard.

Don't get me wrong it is a hard course but Flynn made it a lot harder than it had to be. I'm really not a fan of the whole flipped classroom thing and I think it was the wrong approach for a class like this. Her tests also seemed to be a lot harder than the other sections. If you're willing to over commit to this class take it if not, run...

Super hard class with a prof that made things so unnecessarily difficult. I emailed her multiple times and she never replied. You're going to have to teach yourself most of the content which is already not ideal for a course like this. Avoid if you can.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I was hesitant about the flipped classroom but it works. I learned a lot about my learning style. It isn't an easy class but Dr. Flynn is very compassionate & a great teacher. The flipped style really works - she has YouTube videos you watch and class time is dedicated to practice. One of the best profs I've had! Put in the time & do the practice.

Its a hard class and if you think this class will be easy with any prof think again, Dr. Flynn teaches in flipped classroom which is actually kinda helpful for building the skills on your own. If you don't get it she's available outside of class and stays with you until you get it. She gives you lots of easy points. Shes the best!

Dr. F is such a kind and caring prof. She does a flipped classroom style (watch vids on content on your own then practice in class). Her exams were really fair and there was an optional group portion which was nice. You're weighted by a lot of things (quiz, participation etc). I don't usually do well in chem but I got an A+ in her class.

I don't understand the low ratings. If someone like me who doesn't understand ANYTHING about chemistry got an A on this course, anyone could. Maybe it was because the course was online but, she was very accomodating and made the midterm and final EASY. (except for midterm 1). There is a 20-30% mark for assignments which boosted my grade A LOT.
She doesn't teach in class, only does examples. Not accessible outside of class. I have tried emailing her several times and she doesn't reply. Would not take again.

She adapted SO well to the online troubles of COVID-19. Her marking scheme was so reasonable and I really loved attending her classes (even though the problems she covered were easier than the exams). I did worse than usual on the 1st midterm and I thought that was it, but the 2nd mt and final went super well and I was able to get 97% final mark

She cares very much about her students and tries her best to please everybody. Exams werent too hard. She does flipped classes and i wasnt too happy with that at first but it genuinely is really helpful and I learned a lot that way. The final exam was only 30% which was really great. Such an awesome caring prof :)

Honestly if you are able to self teach, Flynn is the way to go. For online she had 40% free easy grades in the form of quizzes and participation. The first midterm was really tough so she made the second midterm and final stupid easy to account for that. She is flexible and open to feedback. I would recommend her. I went into the final with a 97.

She teaches a flipped classroom style which means you are supposed to learn the content before class on your own and you do practice problems in class. If learning on your own is not something you like or are good at I would not recommend her as your prof. Her tests are fair and there is an opportunity for participation marks.

Flynn's flipped classroom is pretty good in theory except she doesn't run her class well. Her exam was very unbalanced in terms of content. I generally felt as though her classes were a waste of time because her teaching was just going over a simple problem in tons of ways while the exam problems are much harder

I would personally avoid Dr. Flynn at all costs. I really disliked her teaching style. She does the flipped style class super poorly. Get ready to watch videos and try to teach yourself most of the course material as her lectures are not very helpful. Her exams were REALLY HARD and not very fair. Even if you study a lot, she will throw curveballs.
She is so nice and good at lecturing. HOWEVER, the final is toooooooooo DIFFICULT !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! IF U CAN, RUN!!!!!!!
Honestly Flipped classroom is so bad. She teaches you through videos which are very outdated. Honesty did not enjoy. Nice Professor bad style of teaching.
Imma repeat this class with another prof,so you tell me how good she is.

Avoid at all costs, Flipped class with tons of wasted time, doesn't go over any orgo 1 material and then tests you mainly on it. YOutube does a way better job whether compared to her class or her videos.

My worst class since last year, flipped classroom can be good but not this one since her videos are so poorly made compared to other videos, and 50% of the time in class is wasted, in class we solve around 3 easy examples and rest of the time is wasted on the screen questions, first midterm is 80% orgo 1, im was an A student and higher till this

She is very nice and a really caring teacher but her class was a little bit boring, in her defense it was the first time for her teaching this class and i think she did a good job considering circumstances.

Her class follows an inverse course model where you learn the material yourself then follow examples she does in class. The exams closely reflected the course material. The weekly online lecture tests were a bit difficult but doable. She gives an optional project worth 10% if you do better on it than the final.

Content is super easy if you put minimum efforts and she gives you bonus questions at each midterm (Midterms are really easy). She's really caring, energetic and nice & wants her class to succeed. She REALLY listens to students' suggestions and will try to improve her class. No textbook required.

Honestly, try to avoid her. She explained the easiest examples in class and gave you the most complicated during exams. You will have to practice on your own a lot. Midterms were fair but it didn't matter because she's a tough grader and her marking scheme is very specific. Final was brutal. She might look nice but I wouldn't take her again. Nah.

If you need to take organic chemistry 2, do yourself a favour and take it with Dr. Flynn. Yes, the class itself is brutal, but she is very clear with her expectations and the flipped class room style is beneficial because you do examples together in class, and you can always watch extra videos if you need. Hard class, but an excellent professor.
She's an excellent professor- take her for organic chemistry forsure !
Honestly, she's such a nice person and has such great energy that the class is never dull. Would definitely take again.

Dr. Flynn is a real gem. Easy to talk to, clear on what she expects you to know for the exams and is willing to give extra credit in the form of projects. She is good at conveying information and I enjoy her teaching style since she makes us think by asking questions instead of shooting information at us like usual lectures.

Flynn is actually so nice and caring and she works hard. She learns from her mistakes and tries really hard to correct them. She's super fun and positive and it means a lot to have a prof who is actually enthusiastic about teaching us. HOWEVER the class was poorly organized and content could have been better. The project worth 10% was blessed!

Do not take BPS 2510 with Dr. Flynn. The course itself is poorly organized, covering only half the material mentioned on syllabus. The midterms were challenging and the quizzes are poorly made. Overall disappointing and challenging (and not in the good way).

You might be fooled by the other students who had her in organic chemistry, but in biopharm, she's awful. Poorly organized, send the powerpoints after the class is started sometimes and her quizzes are poorly done.

The Fox+Flynn combo for orgo I & II made the courses so much easier than expected. Flynn's class was challenging, but her exams were super fair. That's what makes her my fav prof. The key to doing well in this class is doing past exams, knowing mechanisms (from orgo I too), & knowing concepts. Also, watch out for trick questions, she loves those.

everyone told me good things about her so I made my timetable around her class. WORST DECISION EVER. RUN AS FAST AS YOU CAN AND TAKE CHANS CLASS! She may be a "better lecturer" than him, but neither teach bc of blended learning so it doesn't matter. you gotta learn yourself, watch her do hard problems in class and answer harder problems on exam

I really liked her teaching, but it's not for everyone. If you have her, make sure you watch the videos she posts before class (this took me a while to figure out and they really help!!) She's always looking to help though and very approachable - orgo is hard and she made me feel comfortable asking lots of questions - even dumb ones

Overall, a good teacher for sure and really knows her stuff. Things that frustrated me overall was the lack of extensive practise sets; chem is a practical subject after all. She was controlling over the online resources and I felt that the in class examples were a too easy compared to the exam. Midterms and final were fair, work load not too bad.
Definitely a hard class but she does a good job going over the main concepts and exceptions to the rules. One of my favorite professors so far.

Difficult. Most of the time you'll feel like you are freestyling on exams. No clear criteria for what you should know. Just know everything you can find. Whatever she can test you on, she will. She does the easy work in class, and tests on the exceptions to every rule you've learned so far and the problems you'll most likely skip when practicing.

Finally a prof I can tolerate and enjoy going to their lectures. It is true people learn better from doing examples, and that is exactly what she does every lecture. Super clear when she explains concepts and is probably the nicest human ever.

Dont go on the comments here. This profile and  is overrated. Rude and unhelpful. Comes off as arrogant at times. Class exams are simple nd easy then comes midterm nd exam, not so easy. Whole new diffiulty level. Dnt knw what else to say. Take ogilvie or chan if you can.

I like Flynn's voice and I didn't mind watching the modules every week. However, just that isn't enough to do well.  If you want an A, do the practice problem sets she posts. Her tests are challenging- you need to practice, practice practice. She puts reactions you've never seen before on the midterms.

Dr. Flynn is an amazing prof. I actually hated chemistry general and tended not to do well in any chem course. I liked her method of "flipped classroom" as it it kinda forces you to sit your butt down and study. IN class she would focus on solving problems instead of explaining which is better. her exams are hard but doable.

The flipped classroom thing does not work. It forces students to spend extra time to self-learn the entire course from her videos (bad) or khan academy. I know they're trying to be innovative with their teaching style, but don't fix what isn't broken. Her midterms will wreck you, but you can get some marks back from Sapling assignments.

We had to watch her videos in Chan's class, and boy, were some of them awful. If you're going to make people learn from Youtube, at least make the videos with clear video and audio.  Not a fan of flipped method.

She definitely cares about her students and their learning. I'm not that fond of the flipped class method. I think her midterms contain content that is harder than what was ever brushed on in class. However, she explains concepts effectively and the course is organized well.

Teaches material effectively and exams do reflect what she teaches for the most part, but that doesn't mean they are necessarily easy. Make sure to watch the modules before class. When studying, look over all her notes and examples, especially problem sets as well. DGDs are very helpful if you don't understand some material and if the TA is good.

I have very mixed feelings about her and this course. As a prof she explains concepts very well, she does her best to teach you the material. However the examples done in class are too easy. You have to take what you learn and practice, practice, practice. Practice and study like your life depends on it. Make sure to understand and not memeorize

Went in with confidence after being in her Orgo 1 class. First midterm was easy and review but the 2nd was substantially harder. There seem to be holes between the material what she gives us to study from and exam questions. Not impossible if you study like a dog. She seems to care about how you do but seems to think tests shoul be very challenging

Really nice and very helpful. Her lectures are very engaging and it makes you pay attention. However, teaches easy material in class and the hard stuff you pretty much have to figure out on your own. Midterms and exam are unbelievably hard, you pretty much have to rely on part marks to hope you pass. In class material much easier than tests.

HER TESTS ARE HARD AS HELL. LEFT ME WITH NIGHTMARES, LIKE YEAH USE EASY QUESTONS IN CLASS, THEN EXPECT US TO DO MECHANISMS FOR REACTIONS WE HAVENT SEEN BEFORE. I GET CHALLENGES, BUT THIS IS JUST BEYOND ABSURD. #SCREWCHEM #IMDONE
Dr. Flynn is a nice and sweet lady. She's a great teacher, and is approachable for help. However, her midterms and exam are, and I use this word seriously .. HARD.

Questions on exams were significantly harder than on assignments and in-class examples. Didn't enjoy the "flipped" classroom style since she went over the easy topics in class and expected students to google how to solve the harder problems. Final exam was ridiculously hard.

Flynn is a really good professor! The course was a flipped classroom, but I found it manageable. You have about 1.5 hours of mandatory homework each week. The midterms were definitely harder than the final exam, but were manageable if you study. She's always available in office hours, and is very down to earth. She wants her students to succeed!

Examples in class are sometimes easier than what she'll test you on and what you see in the problem sets. She mostly shows just basics in class but the rest is on you. Nice lady but is sometimes misleading. Told us we were responsible for knowing everything from Orgo 1 with little guidance on what was more important and relevant to Orgo 2.

I have been reading her reviews and while she is nice, expext nothing from her. She makes you learn all the material beforehand, gives you very simple and similar questions in class, and expects you to know more and beyond in the midterms and exams. Midterms were fair if you understand the material, the exam is absolute hell.
I will never take a class with Flynn again. Will not help you if you do not help her with her research. Flipped classroom format is abysmal. In-class activities much easier than exam questions.

Looking back at my two semesters with Alison Flynn I can't say how much I respect this professor, her cleverness the way she teaches... I look back @ it all now and think wow who would've thought I would become a fan of Organic chemistry. It is my easiest &favourite subject now I thank her so much for that. Class,problemsets,pastmids,podcasts-- A+

Flynn is honestly the best prof I had first year. Every lecture was interactive and she was an all-around fun person. If you have ANY questions, she will get you an answer. The homework can be tough but it essentially ensures studying which is perfect.

Amazing professor! Probably one of the best professors I've had. She is very clear on what is expected from her students, and is very fair in her grading. There is always room for easy marks through participation and homework, so take advantage. Midterms and final conveyed course material very well-no surprises. Final was definitely more difficult.
One of my favourite profs at the uni so far.  Walked out of every lecture having learned something.

Heard she was good but since teaching style change, class is useless. Watched random disorganized videos before lectures and learned even less in class. Throws random curve balls on exams. Didn't teach about half the content (said it wouldn't be on exams) then sent out an email 2 days before the final saying it would.

After all the hype from her teaching in orgo I, I thought she would be a lot better. Really don't like how she does really simply examples in class but then puts a lot more difficult ones on the midterms and final. I took Ogilvie for orgo I and he is by far more straight forward with no tricks on his exams.

She is an overrated prof, She plays it very simple in class and her assignments and midterms are brutal. She is also very rude and not at all helpful. She thinks she's funny but i know how rude she can be, if you can please take oligive william

Didn't like the flipped teaching method, I found it made things more complicated and the expectations for exams weren't clear.  Pre-class tests on Sapling were super confusing and then content often wasn't explained in the videos.  She's good at answering questions if you go to office hours though. Upside:  she posts lecture recordings online

Honestly i don't why shes's over rated. I would admit that she is crystal clear in her lectures but she is really rude and not really helpful. her midterms and finals are tough. Do make use of the book.

The best lecturer I've ever had. Eventhough I dont agree with having to study the labs for the final, she still found a way to make it relatively easy.  Dont get me wrong , her exams are TOUGH, but shes always there to help.

Overall, she's a good prof. Her classes are fun and her use of sapling and top hat boosts you. Her second midterm and exam were tricky. I like how she has videos you watch before class so you have an idea of what's going on. She's also very approachable. I wish she did more complex examples in class to better prepare us for midterms and exam!

Great Prof, tough class. Fun, clear lectures and she makes herself available for questions. Her participation questions (quizzes) during her lectures are awesome. Quizzes & online assignments made for relatively easy marks, but the 2nd midterm and final exam were difficult.  Pay attention, attend DGDs, and do practice questions until you're sick.

Dr. Flynn is a good professor. The main thing to address is the inconsistency throughout the course; she may present something in class, but then do something different in her assignments. This was very frustrating for those of us going on to take Orgo 3, as some concepts were left unclear. Final was fair, Top Hat rocks!

Amazing Prof!! She really wants everyone to do well. Teaches the class in a flipped format so you mainly take up example questions in class. Watch the videos and do the pre-class tests  easy marks. Assignments can be a little hard at times. Do the problems sets throughout the semester and before midterms final and you'll do great.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Great lecturer, conveys info well, backwards format helps learning and understanding. Exams are quite difficult, but it's Orgo, so expect it. Lots of practice helps. She was very friendly and accommodating.

Her lectures are more like DGDs because you're doing TopHat examples the entire time, and her videos are not that loud. She does the easiest examples in class and you could probably skip them all if it wasn't for participation. Sapling is a pain and takes forever to finish, but the assignments and pre-class tests are easy marks. Tests are very easy

Flynn is awesome! She made me loved orgo. Don't get me wrong, orgo is not easy, but it is managable with Flynn. She provides you with multiple resourses to do well in the course. Her tests are very fair of what needs to be known, and there are always bonuses! She also has a good sense of humour when need be. You won't regret taking orgo with her!

Excellent prof. Flipped classroom format is effective. Do the lecturesvideos at home and prepare to practice some of the harder examples in class - she's there to explain them! Do everything that is provided (problem sets, past exams, etc.). The material is very tough but she does a good job at conveying it. Sometimes rushes concepts though.

You have a pre-class test and assignment due ONLINE every week (annoying but really does help bring your mark up). Go to class!! Clicker questions are huge (5% of your mark is basically given to you). Tests do match what she teaches in class but are tough so you need to be good at everything. She posts A LOT of extra questions and online help vids.

For spectroscopy chemistry, her teaching style does not convey the course material well at all and you are left either to learn on your own or use the textbook to properly learn the material. Her teaching conveys the idea that she herself does not understand the material properly. Midterms and Finals were impossible.

Professor Flynn is amazing! She is very clear in her expectations and tells you exactly what you need to know. Watch her videos before going to class and you are set! It's really easy to approach her to ask her questions and she really cares about her students and them succeeding! Her dance moves are pretty awesome as well!! :)
Prof Flynn is AMAZING, she genuinely cares about her students and the course is set up for you to succeed. Watch the preclass videos, take notes from them, then the lecture portion is a breeze.

Professor Flynn is the BEST prof I have EVER had!! She makes things really clear and she makes class as interesting and fun as possible. I really, really recommend trying to get her as an organic chemistry prof. It's a tough course but if you take it with her, and apply yourself, you will do well! Can't say enough good things!
SHE IS THE BEST :) Tests are fair and she is very clear about her expectations!

Great prof! Her explanations were clear and she allows your best mark on exams as the highest percentage, and your worst mark as the lowest percentage, so it's easier to get a better grade. Although, you need to do your homework! I HIGHLY suggest doing the “practice problems”. Trust me its worth your time when understanding the material.

Really amazing prof. I don't know why people complain about toughness. there is so much flexibility on what your exams/midterms are worth. great explanations. I love the fact that she gives assignments with answers. Gives so many resources. Expectations are very simple.

Best prof EVER, super clear, super down to earth, explains the hell out of absolutely everything, available outside of class, just awesome. She's currently doing research on new teaching methods, so is always on top of her game. Uses a TON of online systems though, top hat, sapling, etc. Not an easy prof, but DEFINITELY fair.

She is the best prof I have ever had. She takes a really difficult concept and makes it accessible and easy and interesting! Her teaching style is really good and clear. Her exams are really fair and she let's you know what to expect.
Amazing prof, she explains things really well and I love going to her class. It is fun and interactive and makes organic chem much easier than typical styles of teaching.
Wonderful professor. She truly cares about her students. Midterms are super fair as long as you put in the work.

The best prof I have had so far. If you are willing to put a lot of effort into the course, she will help you do well. She really pays attention to the clarity of her answers and never makes you feel stupid for having the wrong answer. The next Orgo prof will have big boots to fill for sure!!

I took and failed this class with another professor. She makes the information so much more accessible to the students and is very knowledgable and personable. Although still not an easy A, you will probably do better in her class because you will understand the subject matter better.
Really good prof. Lectures were really clear and straightforward. Midterms were fair but the final was challenging.

She's a great prof. She gives you all kinds of great resources and her marking is fair. If you found Orgo I difficult, you may find this class difficult as well, but if you work hard, you will get a good mark because prof Flynn gives you everything you need to do well.

Lectures were very interesting and the grading scheme was pretty fair. The midterm and final were challenging, but just do the practice problem sets she provided and the sapling questions, and you should be set! Didn't touch the textbook once. :)
Horrible Class. She was such a great teacher in Orgo, but her teaching style for Spec is HORRIBLE! DO NOT TAKE SPEC WITH HER!
Amazing prof. Makes the material easy and fun to learn! Loved her pre-class tests and assignments. Helped boost my grade :) LOVE FLYNN!

We do a lot of practise problems in class but she is as useful as an answer key when it comes to solving these problems in class. What I mean by that is that she will tell you the answer but will not answer how or why she got what she got. It is as if she expects us to study concepts that she fails to teach in class. She is not a good professor imo

Very good prof. EXCELLENT course. It's really challenging and the material is heavy and tough but she is very fair and goes out of her way to provide students with ample opportunities to get good grades. I wasn't very good at orgo, but she made me love to course :)

Explains the material well, stops to answer questions and really cares about the success of her students. Uses video-recorded explanations for the main concepts and then builds on them in class. The midterm questions weren't a surprise.

Love this prof! Had her for CHM1311 and 1321, and I'm sad that I won't have her for orgo 2. She is really clear in her explanations, but she doesn't give you all the answers. You had to learn how to do problems, which is more useful than just copying and example seen in class. Makes you LEARN, not memorize.

She explains things well and gives you lots of practise. The midterms are tough and long, so if you are not good at chem, I don't think you'll get a good course mark. The exam was very easy. It is a shame she won't be teaching next year

I had her for 1311 and now 1321, amazing proff. Super clear notes, stimulating lectures and great personality. She really goes the extra mile to help you learn and her midterms/exams are straight forward. As for reaching her after class she was pregnant this semester so obv it's difficult, but first semester she was always free. FLYNN FOR THE WIN !

She's clear & concise. But she's overrated; her teaching style is like most profs, but she doesn't even give the time or day outside of office hours;emailing is not helpful. She's a good teaching only in class, but outside she's impersonal, and I'm pretty sure I can reach all my other science profs much easier who have more/bigger classes than her.

She was very straight forward and helpful. Midterms and exams reflected exactly what she taught. One of the best profs I've had. Good enough to switch in to her class at 2 am for second semester after having her for first semester.

Had her for CHM1311 as well. She is a great teacher, and explains the basics in class. However, the assignments are much harder than ex. given in class. At first this frustrated me, but it actually makes you LEARN the material, rather than memorize it. I find her teaching method effective. You just need to take the time to review and study.

Very good prof! Had her for Orgo 1 and 2. In her notes she doesn't feed you the answers, she gives you ways of figuring out the answers to problems! Highly recommend her. Make sure to do the assignments and her old midterms and your golden. Her notes are amazing an crystal clear, best ive ever had. She always finds a way to keep the class
Great prof! Interesting and stimulating lectures. Makes chemistry interesting. Her step by step approach to solving problems is great! Always willing to help. Highly recommend this prof!
Compared to the other first year chemistry profs she was tough, but knows what she's talking about. She also prepares you well for future chemistry classes.

One great thing about her teaching and examination method is that even if you memorize every mechanism from every assignment and previous test, she will still test you with questions that will force your use of problem solving ability. Bravo. Also, highly accommodating to all students' needs. Thanks prof Flynn.
She's hotter then a bunsen burner set to full power

I think Prof Flynn is the best prof at u.ottawa, you get to learn organic chemistry and get a good grade at the same time. Just LISTEN in class and PRACTICE(alot!) on the assignments and you'll do good.

I feel like she rushes through the material, and I feel confused when I attempt the assignments. Her exams, however, contain no surprises. I felt that  listening to Boddy's (other CHM2120 prof) podcasts, and youtube really helped with Flynn's exams + assignments.

Out of all the first year chem profs, her exams were the easiest. She goes over really simple questions in lectures but make the mastering chemistry questions overbearingly hard, this will give you a sense that you're not ready for the exams. Don't worry her exams are very fair and are the same difficulty as the questions she go over in lectures.

Awesome prof! She is very clear about all of her subject matter and there are no surprises on the midterms or exams. Although some found the final to be difficult, all subject matter was reviewed extensively. She always gives time for problems during lecture and walks around helping those who are stuck. This is a very good quality for a prof!
Hard class, but good teacher. U need to memorize alot for exams and practise all the assignments and practise exams.
Pretty good prof. Midterms were fair, exam was hard.
Very clear and helpful. Races though the last sections and dwells on review though.
Amazing organic chemistry professor, you'd be crazy not to take orgo with her.

Textbook is only needed to do the chapter questions, otherwise Professor Flynn explains everything extremely well! Her final was more difficult than her midterms but fair. Labs are a breeze and boost up your mark. Do the SUGGESTED questions, not mastering chemistry questions for midterms/exams and you'll be fine!
Very nice....almost too nice. I found it really hard to pay attention in class. Her tests are harder than her homework but if you understand the concepts, its really not that bad.

Professor Flynn may have gone a little slower than the other classes, but she made sure everybody understood the concepts.  Her final was way harder than expected, as the midterms were fairly easy, but altogether, great prof  :)

She is a nice prof I'll give her that, but for starters her lectures aren't really interesting. She tries to teach, but everyone looses interest(Unless it's a tophatmonocle question) and everyone begins to doze off and do miscellaneous things such as gaming. Her mid terms/ final are pure suicide. She throws WAY too many curve ball questions.

She makes chemistry fun! I've read the comments about her exams being unfair or trying to "screw people over", I would have to disagree..  Personally though, I found the assignments great practice for exams. Advice: go to class and practice.

She is a good teacher; neat notes, answers questions well, and clear when she lectures. Her midterms are designed to trick you, and she tends to present questions that are unfamiliar to see if you understand the concept thoroughly. However, she's hard to get help from outside class, and won't give you the time and day outside of office hours.

Excellent professor and just a great person overall. Organic is tough but she actually makes it very enjoyable and interesting. Super helpful during office hours and is flexible with appointments. Super down to earth, knowledgeable, fun,.. just awesome. Take her class you won't regret it. Class notes are sufficient for studying, do the assignments!

Prof Flynn is GREAT! She's really nice and easy to go to with questions. Doing the optional assignments on her website make the midterms a lot more bearable. Another great thing is she actually likes to teach (who woulda thought?!), so her lectures & notes are really clear and the class is interactive.  Overall: awesome prof!

EXPECTS TOO MUCH !! TOUGH MARKER !!! IF YOU HAVE ORGANIC II WITH HER JUST DROP IT ! HER LECTURES ARE ALL NICE AND CLEAR BUT HER EXAMS ARE  A SUICIDE !  DO NOT EXPECT HER TO BELL CURVE YOUR MARK !!! YOU MIGHT GET AN EXTRA 1 OR 2 POINTS AT THE END , BUT NOT WORTH TAKING THE CLASS WITH HER!

J'ai trouvé que ses examens étaient extrêmement difficiles après maintes et maintes révisions. Je suis désolé mais on ne veut pas tous faire un ph.d en chimie et c'est pas un concours de qui fait couler le plus d'élèves...

Flynn is an EXCELLENT organic chemistry prof. Her notes are very clean and she knows exactly what she is talking about. If you're confused with anything I strongly suggest you go talk to her and she will clear it up ASAP. Tests are difficult, you really need to think on your feet for them. Be sure to attend the classes and colour-code you notes! :)

AMAZING. The course is tough in general but I've hated chem all my life and she somehow managed to turn it into one of my favourite subjects. You'll never have anyone better at explaining complex orgo mechanisms than prof Flynn. Labs will bring you down but that's inevitable in orgo 1. Switch into her class noow, you won't regret it.

As a lecturer she was great, used a lot of examples and provided students with optional assigment, HOWEVER her exams were absolutely ridiculous! they were nothing like the assignment and were way harder than dr. ogilvie's exams. I got a sense that she wanted to give studen'ts a challenge fbut for organic I the class is challenge enough!

Great prof!!!! has high expectations so a lot of hard work is necessary. gives clear and concise notes in class(textbook not required. just do the assignments,quizzes and stuff. Best thing why i would recommend the prof is that she gives her students lots of opportunities to score marks thru clickers and weighing of midterms and exams are flexible.

I really don't see a problem with this class, pretty much everyone I knew got A's or up. I don't see many people giving advice on here but heres what I did: Do all assignments twice. First time for learning, 2nd time for mastering the material. So that means doubling the recommended studying time she gave. I got A+, but at a great cost.. life sucks

I really believe prof Flynn's expectations are way beyond what most typical students can handle.  I agree her final was ridiculous.  I feel like I was part of a teaching experiment.  What sucks is we are paying big money for this and I also feel taken and ripped off!  Her course blows.

I found this course to be very unfortunate.  I felt that I grasped the course material pretty well.  The class notes and assignments were straightforward. What wasn't was the final exam.  I feel totally ripped off of marks.  Organic has a reputation for being challenging-fine, but to screw us on the final like she did is not fine!

Though professor Flynn is a good prof, I felt that her expectations for the class on the final exam were not well conveyed.  Her practice final was a joke compared to this year's final. Obviously she is more concerned with the class % than individual success- This is too common an occurrence at Ottawa U. Balance the damn tests!

If you want to LEARN organic chemistry, please register with prof Flynn. If you would rather memorize your way through a inherently useless degree and expect the real world to ask you to memorize anything (ever!)...then don't take prof Flynn's class because it will destroy you. Organic chemistry now makes sense after Prof Flynn- thanks!

Professor Flynn seems like a good person and gives great notes.  Unfortunately, they only give you clues - I really don't think she wants people to get good grades. Her 1st midterm was a disaster, 2nd one was a bit easier but her final was horrible. Thanks to this experience I now hate chemistry. Good luck to all who get stuck with Flynn.

She seemed to be a nice enough person.  Lectures were entertaining and notes were clear. However the midterms and final were unpredictable - not like the assignments.  It appeared that there was an intent to screw students out of their grades. Has left me feeling negative about science at Ottawa U. I should have gone to a science based university.

I agree with several of the comments below.  Flynn is a decent lecturer, however as a prof she puts too much emphasis on problem-based learning leaving those of us who are not natural chemists scratching our heads.  The final looked like nothing that was given to us on assignments and was made intentionally difficult to sabotage the final class %.

I agree with many of the comments below.  Flynn is a good prof, but because the final she gave was far beyond my abilities, and doesn't look like any of the assignments, I'll probably be stuck taking this class again.  I'll hope for a more fair final.  Typical undergrad BS games profs play :(

Though I did every assignment (repeatedly), attended every lecture (scored 95% on ACE assn) I did very poorly in the course.  I found the first midterm unrealistic, the 2nd easier (probably to bring up the low marks from the first midterm), but the final was just stupid.  She picked every obscure example she could find.Look out!  Not easy at all!!
Ignore the comment below's ranking. Don't know what happened with that, but if you want to learn organic chemistry, then take it with Flynn :)

Professor Flynn notes are ridiculous! They are so neat and easy to follow. She explained everything so well. Midterms are easy to ace (if you did all the practice assignments and studied hard). Final was alright, but definitely need to study really hard for as a lot of the material was shoved in the last 3 weeks of the course. My fav prof though :)

Je n'ai jamais détesté la chimie plus qu'après ce cours. L'examen final était très difficile et je trouve que ce cours n'est pas nécessaire pour mon programme. Les mécanismes sont difficiles à apprendre et la difficulté des devoirs n'est pas comparable à celle de l'examen. Les clicker sont aussi des contraptions frustrantes qui n'on rien ajouté.
She was awesome. Switched to her class from Gamborrotta and is the best decision I ever made. Explains things very well. Just study hard you will make it. One of the best prof there.
Prof Flynn is by far THE BEST professor I've had at UofO. Her notes are clear and concise. She always conveys the subject matter very well.

Excellent teacher, her clarity and organization is top tier. She's loves to teach, she loves her students, but she can be picky with her marking. If you're taking organic chemistry make sure you have Flynn, she rekindled my love of chemistry after General Chemistry. Off the record she's got a huge caboose lol :P

Excellent prof! Obviously really loves what she's teaching and likes to teach it. Uses lots of big props to explain. She uses a stylus and lots of different colors to show the molecules, but you don't have access to them anywhere after the class. Make friends to get the notes from if you miss. Also, you have to pay to do the online quizes. Not cool

Her lecture notes are WAY TOO NEAT :P This is one of the best prof I've had! Crystal-clear teaching, answers all questions. If your taking CHM1321, make sure you take her! You won't regret it. You have to come to class though, because she doens't post notes online. Heavy workload,so don't fall behind in her class. Study hard, and you'll get A :)
Really great prof! Great at explaining things and uses lots of examples and props to help explain things
Amazing notes, very clear, don't need to read much of the textbook because she explains everything so well, answers class questions courteously and fully answers all questions. Amazing Prof!

Amazing prof! She takes her time to explain the material very clearly and makes sure that everyone (or mostly everyone) understands before moving on- which is rare in university, especially for a first year 200 person science class. She even came to the labs and made sure everyone was having a good time! Incredible!

Awesome prof! Very helpful, has lots of office hours and good TAs. Evaluations are fair but you need to know you're stuff. Small easy assignments here and there help you get a few percents to get your mark up. Answers questions Really well. Discussion forum on Virtual Campus really helpful. I Strongly recommend this prof! Also, good sense of humor.

Best prof I've ever had. Teaching and notes are amazing,really easy to understand. She's very nice and approachable,and knows her subject really well. Be prepared to work a lot - absolutely do all the practice questions. I didn't think the final was that bad this year, just the format and length threw everyone off. Tests are challenging but doable.

She is an amazing prof! I find it unfortunate that she made the final for this year IMPOSSIBLE compared to the final exam in 2007. I didn't find this years final to be fair at all. Which is unfortunate because she is incredibly nice and very helpful. Will always answer questions and wants everyone to do well (well except for this years final).

She is an excellent prof who does her best to ensure you understand all the concepts. Be warned, you might think things are going good in the class, but don't underestimate the exam. On the midterms, you could slide by studying for a couple days, but you better know how to synthesize the ATOMIC BOMB in order to pass the final!!! Well not exactly...
No Comments

She's a really great professor, cares about her students and puts in a lot of effort to make sure the class does well. The course load is heavier than average, but it was one of my favorite classes. Had her for CHM1321 last year, and she was just as awesome then as she was this year. She's also super nice, don't hesitate to ask her questions!
One of the best profs at Ottawa U.
Best Prof ever!!!
Best chem prof ever. Her lessons are very easy to follow and she made the material so easy to understand that I rarely used the text book. Doing the practice problems helps alot too.
Very good prof!
She was a very good professor, knows how to keep your attention throughout the semester.  I like her way of teaching and if you put in the work it is easy to do good in her class

Uber motivated, huge line-ups of students in front of her office door because she is VERY helpful when you go see her and pumps the motivation in you to.  Tries as much as she can to make spectroscopy fun.
PLEASE TEACH ORGANIC II !!!!!!!!!!
Prof. Flynn is definitely the best prof ever. Learned a lot in her class, unlike some other profs.
She's the best prof ever !!  I love her ! we all loved her and you'll love her so take her !!!!!!!!!!!!
Absolutely fantastic. She deserves an award.

She's an awesome prof, definitely the best I've had in university. She cares about her students and explains well. You have to study for your exams but they're fair. I walked into the class thinking it would be brutal because I didn't like organic chem but it turned out to be one of my best classes!

Love her!  She really goes out of her way to help people understand the material, and her notes and lectures are crystal clear.  Exams and midterms reflect what you cover in class, and STUDY THE ASSIGNMENTS!!
Very well organized, approachable, kind and very solid in her understanding of topic. She deserves to be recognized. Best science teacher/prof I've had over my education of 1.5 degrees.
